UGHELLI – Mr. Andrew Aganbi, a politician and entertainment guru based in Warri, Delta State has commended President Muhammadu Buhari on the appointment of Chief Bernard Okumagba as Managing Director of Niger Delta Development Commission. Aganbi, who gave the commendation in Warri on Thursday, said the appointment of Okumagba as NDDC MD was ordained by God and accomplished by Buhari. He noted that Buhari was meticulous in choosing capable hands to run the affairs of the NDDC to accelerate the development of the Niger Delta region and urged the people of the region to give their maximum support to the newly constituted Board of the NDDC. Aganbi emphasised the need to support the new board of the NDDC for effective operation and serve the people better by way of spreading viable projects across the communities of the Niger Delta.